Package wt.occurrence

Defines the capability to uniquely distinguish one occurrence of an object within some complex structure from another occurrence of that same object within the same structure using OccurrenceService.

See: Description

Package wt.occurrence Description

Defines the capability to uniquely distinguish one occurrence of an object within some complex structure from another occurrence of that same object within the same structure using OccurrenceService.

Occurrences may be:

  • UsesOccurrence
  • PathOccurrence
  • CombinedPathOccurrence

OccurrenceData may be:

  • UsesOccurrenceData, which includes:
    • UsesOccurrenceDocumentation
    • UsesOccurrenceUserIBAs
  • PathOccurrenceData, which includes:
    • PathOccurrenceDocumentation
    • PathOccurrenceUserIBAs
  • CombinedPathOccurrenceData, which includes:
    • CombinedPathOccurrenceDocumentation
    • CombinedPathOccurrenceUserIBAs

See wt.part as the reference implementation of Occurrences:

  • PartUsesOccurrence
  • PartPathOccurrence
  • PartCombinedPathOccurrence
